1
00:00:55,000 --> 00:01:00,000
The Story of Minglan

2
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:02,842
Episode 29

3
00:01:17,584 --> 00:01:18,904
You're finally here!

4
00:01:20,819 --> 00:01:22,459
We heard you are coming,

5
00:01:22,459 --> 00:01:23,226
and our entire family's

6
00:01:23,226 --> 00:01:24,980
been full of glee!

7
00:01:24,980 --> 00:01:25,723
The Old Madam ate

8
00:01:25,723 --> 00:01:27,449
an extra half-bowl of rice yesterday!

9
00:01:28,740 --> 00:01:31,370
That means she really missed me!

10
00:01:31,370 --> 00:01:32,050
If it hadn't been for

11
00:01:32,050 --> 00:01:34,116
Hong'er's mother's illness

12
00:01:34,116 --> 00:01:36,620
dragging over a month to recover,

13
00:01:36,620 --> 00:01:38,530
I would have come a long time ago!

14
00:01:38,530 --> 00:01:40,235
Old Madam's been waiting for us

15
00:01:40,235 --> 00:01:41,190
for a long time. Let's go in!

16
00:01:41,190 --> 00:01:43,910
Hurry now. Hurry and let me greet her!

17
00:01:46,390 --> 00:01:49,120
Try this cup of tea now.

18
00:02:01,680 --> 00:02:03,460
Great tea.

19
00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:08,510
We've been here for half the day already.

20
00:02:08,510 --> 00:02:11,080
Why don't we see your little granddaughter?

21
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,920
Is she not at home?

22
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,650
She's sick.

23
00:02:15,590 --> 00:02:17,630
What's the illness?

24
00:02:19,060 --> 00:02:21,260
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

25
00:02:21,260 --> 00:02:23,530
So I could go take a look?

26
00:02:23,530 --> 00:02:25,430
Nothing too serious,

27
00:02:25,430 --> 00:02:27,880
just some headache and light fever.

28
00:02:27,880 --> 00:02:31,620
Your Hong'er can deal with it.

29
00:02:32,360 --> 00:02:34,640
You sly lady!

30
00:02:40,790 --> 00:02:41,406
Miss,

31
00:02:41,615 --> 00:02:43,265
the sister from Old Madam's room

32
00:02:43,265 --> 00:02:44,105
sent a message.

33
00:02:44,200 --> 00:02:45,171
It says that the Young Master of the He House

34
00:02:45,171 --> 00:02:46,818
is waiting for you at Shouan Hall,

35
00:02:46,818 --> 00:02:48,439
and he won't leave.

36
00:02:49,120 --> 00:02:50,760
Didn't I tell you what to tell them,

37
00:02:50,760 --> 00:02:53,120
Tell them I'm sick and asleep.

38
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:55,040
I already did, and he left.

39
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,190
But not long after, he came back again.

40
00:02:57,190 --> 00:02:59,147
He said he told the kitchen to make fish stew

41
00:02:59,147 --> 00:03:01,700
for you to eat.

42
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:04,128
What a weird man!

43
00:03:04,128 --> 00:03:05,551
What time is it now?

44
00:03:06,060 --> 00:03:07,919
The fish market must have closed long ago.

45
00:03:07,919 --> 00:03:10,067
How can he make fish stew?

46
00:03:10,290 --> 00:03:12,704
He said he brought the fish from Youyang.

47
00:03:12,704 --> 00:03:14,064
Your favorite, Miss.

48
00:03:39,730 --> 00:03:41,770
This really is fresh fish from Youyang's river?

49
00:03:41,770 --> 00:03:44,240
How is it available in Bianjing?

50
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,520
I remember back in Youyang that

51
00:03:45,520 --> 00:03:46,860
you love to eat fish soup.

52
00:03:46,860 --> 00:03:47,898
When I found out I would accompany Grandmother

53
00:03:47,898 --> 00:03:49,244
to the capital to visit you,

54
00:03:49,244 --> 00:03:51,284
I went to Youyang to fish a few.

55
00:03:51,790 --> 00:03:52,775
I put them in a big crock

56
00:03:52,775 --> 00:03:53,510
to put in the carriage,

57
00:03:53,510 --> 00:03:54,430
and I added some

58
00:03:54,430 --> 00:03:56,660
clean water every day.

59
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:57,781
When we arrived,

60
00:03:57,781 --> 00:03:59,307
two were still alive.

61
00:03:59,307 --> 00:04:01,007
I heard you were sick.

62
00:04:01,460 --> 00:04:02,940
So I hurried and made fish soup

63
00:04:02,940 --> 00:04:05,540
to bring to you, so you can warm your stomach.

64
00:04:05,990 --> 00:04:07,910
Why did you bother yourself?

65
00:04:07,910 --> 00:04:09,430
Nobody in the world

66
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:11,750
will not get sick.

67
00:04:11,750 --> 00:04:15,010
Just a slight fever, and no need to worry about.

68
00:04:15,010 --> 00:04:16,578
You ate your heart out,

69
00:04:16,578 --> 00:04:18,440
and harmed your state of mind.

70
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:19,680
You need good restoration.

71
00:04:20,085 --> 00:04:21,085
After you're well,

72
00:04:21,520 --> 00:04:22,440
the flowers will be blooming everywhere,

73
00:04:22,448 --> 00:04:24,800
and you can leave the house to pray to the gods.

74
00:04:25,780 --> 00:04:28,208
Having an outing in the great scenery out in the open plain,

75
00:04:28,544 --> 00:04:30,064
and your heart and soul will naturally be nourished.

76
00:04:31,140 --> 00:04:32,420
You need to eat this soup while it's hot.

77
00:04:32,727 --> 00:04:34,790
I went through such trouble to fish them.

78
00:04:35,300 --> 00:04:36,924
It was so cold by the river at night.

79
00:04:37,730 --> 00:04:38,930
If you don't eat it all,

80
00:04:39,538 --> 00:04:41,781
you owe me for my suffering a chill.

81
00:04:46,780 --> 00:04:49,210
Actually, I didn't suffer any chill.

82
00:04:49,210 --> 00:04:50,115
These fish, actually I bought them

83
00:04:50,115 --> 00:04:52,140
from the fishermen by the river.

84
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:54,760
I didn't go through much trouble.

85
00:05:00,380 --> 00:05:01,620
There you go.

86
00:05:01,840 --> 00:05:03,150
Smile a bit.

87
00:05:03,150 --> 00:05:04,825
Clear your mind and release toxins

88
00:05:04,825 --> 00:05:05,470
and live a long life.

89
00:05:41,130 --> 00:05:43,240
Don't make tea right now.

90
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,680
What's going on?

91
00:05:44,680 --> 00:05:45,769
You need to let me know

92
00:05:45,769 --> 00:05:47,488
so I can be at ease!

93
00:05:48,580 --> 00:05:50,227
Aunt does not need to be at ease.

94
00:05:50,227 --> 00:05:51,866
I need to be at ease.

95
00:05:56,700 --> 00:05:59,550
You need to be at ease.

96
00:05:59,550 --> 00:06:00,230
Then you can just

97
00:06:00,230 --> 00:06:02,060
go to your home to make tea.

98
00:06:02,060 --> 00:06:04,870
You come to my place to make tea for whom?

99
00:06:05,440 --> 00:06:06,760
I can't be at ease at home.

100
00:06:07,540 --> 00:06:09,432
I can only be at ease

101
00:06:09,432 --> 00:06:10,416
making tea with you.

102
00:06:36,790 --> 00:06:38,550
The first cup spilled to the ground,

103
00:06:38,550 --> 00:06:39,440
to honor my mother.

104
00:06:49,280 --> 00:06:52,590
Second cup, may Auntie enjoy.

105
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:19,470
Third cup, I enjoy it.

106
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:30,147
We're done praying to God.

107
00:07:30,147 --> 00:07:30,828
Time to go home.

108
00:07:32,210 --> 00:07:33,740
Go home?

109
00:07:35,300 --> 00:07:36,249
Then

110
00:07:36,249 --> 00:07:39,250
What about your mother's matter?

111
00:07:39,250 --> 00:07:40,890
You said you tried to tell your father

112
00:07:40,890 --> 00:07:41,954
and it might work out,

113
00:07:41,954 --> 00:07:42,994
so I should be at ease.

114
00:07:43,890 --> 00:07:45,490
Now you come drink tea and leave.

115
00:07:45,490 --> 00:07:47,250
How can I be at ease?

116
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:49,930
You made this trip

117
00:07:49,930 --> 00:07:51,667
just to make tea and drink,

118
00:07:51,667 --> 00:07:53,290
and then go home?

119
00:07:53,290 --> 00:07:54,950
Yes. I came to the monastery,

120
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:56,330
and now I'm going home.

121
00:08:00,840 --> 00:08:02,840
Why do you bother walking, Big Madam?

122
00:08:02,840 --> 00:08:03,277
We can have the carriage driver bring the carriage

123
00:08:03,277 --> 00:08:05,154
in all the way to the mountain gate

124
00:08:05,180 --> 00:08:06,620
and you will be spared some travel.

125
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:07,770
You know nothing.

126
00:08:07,770 --> 00:08:08,530
Using your own feet,

127
00:08:08,530 --> 00:08:10,010
climbing up step by step.

128
00:08:10,310 --> 00:08:12,580
That shows more sincerity!

129
00:08:15,870 --> 00:08:17,400
Sheng House's Sixth Miss!

130
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:19,590
Greetings, Big Madam Wu of the Liang House!

131
00:08:19,590 --> 00:08:20,350
Greetings!

132
00:08:20,350 --> 00:08:21,790
We are so fated!

133
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:24,320
I always run into you.

134
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,590
I think that the gods and spirits watch over it!

135
00:08:26,590 --> 00:08:28,352
What a joy.

136
00:08:28,750 --> 00:08:30,420
How is your health lately, Big Madam?

137
00:08:30,420 --> 00:08:31,920
Great.

138
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:32,405
Look.

139
00:08:32,405 --> 00:08:33,882
The weather's getting warmer.

140
00:08:34,170 --> 00:08:36,000
By Jinming Pond, the grass is green

141
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:36,890
and the flowers have bloomed.

142
00:08:37,085 --> 00:08:38,685
And you play such great jiju

143
00:08:38,685 --> 00:08:41,347
so you must come and help!

144
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,310
I don't feel so well lately.

145
00:08:45,310 --> 00:08:46,773
I'm afraid I can't play jiju.

146
00:08:47,191 --> 00:08:49,421
I don't want to ruin your great record,

147
00:08:49,421 --> 00:08:50,381
so I won't go.

148
00:08:50,550 --> 00:08:53,940
What's wrong? Not feeling well?

149
00:08:53,940 --> 00:08:55,460
I have great wild ginseng

150
00:08:55,460 --> 00:08:56,980
and when I return home,

151
00:08:56,980 --> 00:08:57,800
I'll have it delivered to your room

152
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:58,610
so you can restore your vitality.

153
00:08:58,630 --> 00:08:59,670
Don't bother.

154
00:08:59,670 --> 00:09:02,356
It's just, it's just a cold.

155
00:09:02,356 --> 00:09:04,461
Thank you for your concern, Big Madam.

156
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:07,769
A cold will be gone in few days.

157
00:09:07,910 --> 00:09:08,710
I'll wait until you're recovered

158
00:09:08,710 --> 00:09:09,910
and hold the jiju match.

159
00:09:09,910 --> 00:09:11,625
We're not in a rush over a few days.

160
00:09:15,470 --> 00:09:16,390
There are words

161
00:09:17,182 --> 00:09:18,554
that you're not telling me.

162
00:09:19,240 --> 00:09:20,097
This isn't

163
00:09:20,097 --> 00:09:21,617
the conduct of our great child.

164
00:09:23,410 --> 00:09:24,770
I went once in previous year

165
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:26,690
because I played jiju for Sister Yanran.

166
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,602
Afterward, I caused quite a stir out of it

167
00:09:32,151 --> 00:09:33,697
and I've reflected upon myself.

168
00:09:34,270 --> 00:09:36,200
I think the troubles came

169
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:37,750
from my showing off,

170
00:09:37,750 --> 00:09:39,430
so now I've cultivated

171
00:09:39,430 --> 00:09:41,580
my temperament to be more calm.

172
00:09:41,580 --> 00:09:42,845
I shouldn't play jiju anymore,

173
00:09:42,845 --> 00:09:44,805
just stay at home and write.

174
00:09:46,540 --> 00:09:48,590
Those idle talkers and gossips?

175
00:09:48,590 --> 00:09:49,800
You should treat them

176
00:09:49,800 --> 00:09:50,740
like bullshit!

177
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:52,725
Why are you taking them in

178
00:09:52,725 --> 00:09:53,860
and caring about them?

179
00:09:53,860 --> 00:09:56,250
Sister Rulan and Molan.

180
00:09:56,250 --> 00:09:58,259
They are not that interested in jiju,

181
00:09:58,259 --> 00:10:00,246
so it's not proper for me to go either.

182
00:10:00,830 --> 00:10:02,670
It might stir some talk

183
00:10:02,670 --> 00:10:04,510
that you hold me in high regard, Countess.

184
00:10:04,510 --> 00:10:05,850
I do hold you in high regard!

185
00:10:05,850 --> 00:10:06,530
So?

186
00:10:06,530 --> 00:10:08,247
Let them talk idly!

187
00:10:10,208 --> 00:10:12,650
Big Madam, I think we should forget it.

188
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,760
I understand.

189
00:10:17,948 --> 00:10:20,000
You're all alone in the courtyard

190
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,000
and it's not easy.

191
00:10:21,334 --> 00:10:22,454
Fine then.

192
00:10:23,190 --> 00:10:24,707
I wanted you to play jiju with me,

193
00:10:24,707 --> 00:10:26,160
but I will not put you in any difficulty.

194
00:10:26,160 --> 00:10:28,263
I'll send an invitation to your home tomorrow

195
00:10:28,263 --> 00:10:31,325
to invite all the sisters.

196
00:10:37,280 --> 00:10:39,140
I wonder if that Countess

197
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:40,520
is fond of our daughter.

198
00:10:41,460 --> 00:10:43,393
Why is she sending an invitation here

199
00:10:43,393 --> 00:10:44,833
each time there's an event?

200
00:10:47,010 --> 00:10:48,239
A jiju match,

201
00:10:48,239 --> 00:10:50,410
and such a formal invitation!

202
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:52,802
It does seem to be so.

203
00:10:53,470 --> 00:10:54,270
Lately,

204
00:10:54,580 --> 00:10:56,100
the Countess comes to the manor often

205
00:10:56,671 --> 00:10:57,671
and we didn't see her coming here

206
00:10:57,671 --> 00:10:58,711
so frequently before.

207
00:11:01,190 --> 00:11:02,230
That's why

208
00:11:03,800 --> 00:11:06,360
she came a few days ago

209
00:11:06,934 --> 00:11:09,170
and it seemed like casual talk,

210
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:11,490
but in reality she wanted to reveal to us

211
00:11:11,490 --> 00:11:13,090
about Qi House and Prince Yong's matter.

212
00:11:14,360 --> 00:11:15,240
In fact

213
00:11:16,648 --> 00:11:18,295
she's implying me.

214
00:11:19,800 --> 00:11:21,720
Telling me not to put my hopes up with Qi House,

215
00:11:22,420 --> 00:11:23,700
the best option

216
00:11:23,700 --> 00:11:25,060
is to be in-laws with her instead.

217
00:11:26,470 --> 00:11:27,510
The invitation says

218
00:11:28,061 --> 00:11:30,381
to have all three Misses come.

219
00:11:31,050 --> 00:11:32,050
I just don't know

220
00:11:32,663 --> 00:11:34,463
which Miss she's fond of.

221
00:11:34,463 --> 00:11:36,258
Of course.

222
00:11:36,258 --> 00:11:38,870
It must be my Rulan!

223
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:40,782
Allow me to say a word

224
00:11:40,782 --> 00:11:42,223
without courting your anger.

225
00:11:42,740 --> 00:11:43,900
From what I have seen these days,

226
00:11:44,625 --> 00:11:46,926
the Countess seems

227
00:11:46,926 --> 00:11:47,966
closer to Sixth Miss.

228
00:11:50,760 --> 00:11:52,640
Close is just being close.

229
00:11:53,820 --> 00:11:56,875
Minglan is just decent at jiju

230
00:11:56,875 --> 00:11:57,995
and that pleases her.

231
00:11:59,350 --> 00:12:01,110
But when it comes to marriage,

232
00:12:01,110 --> 00:12:03,310
that's different.

233
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:05,160
It's like you

234
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,120
raise a cat or dog.

235
00:12:06,710 --> 00:12:08,171
You are so pleased with it,

236
00:12:08,171 --> 00:12:09,051
but it's not like you're going to marry

237
00:12:09,051 --> 00:12:09,731
that cat or dog

238
00:12:09,731 --> 00:12:11,131
to your own son.

239
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:17,750
Mother.

240
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:19,310
I don't want to go attend that jiju match.

241
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:21,580
So much dust at the place

242
00:12:21,580 --> 00:12:22,500
and it's suffocating.

243
00:12:23,210 --> 00:12:23,930
Each time I go,

244
00:12:23,930 --> 00:12:25,441
I'm covered with mud all over.

245
00:12:26,550 --> 00:12:27,550
I'm definitely not going.

246
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:29,210
Silly.

247
00:12:29,638 --> 00:12:31,078
What did I tell you?

248
00:12:31,230 --> 00:12:33,030
Sixth Young Master Liang is interested in you

249
00:12:33,364 --> 00:12:35,284
and that's a God given chance.

250
00:12:35,770 --> 00:12:37,090
But Big Madam is there.

251
00:12:37,456 --> 00:12:38,632
She won't approve of

252
00:12:38,632 --> 00:12:40,152
Sixth Young Master Liang and I being close.

253
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:43,630
As long as you're more daring

254
00:12:43,770 --> 00:12:44,890
and do things more furtively...

255
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,444
Last time at the Gu House,

256
00:12:47,444 --> 00:12:48,450
you and Young Master Liang

257
00:12:48,450 --> 00:12:49,810
made poetry too.

258
00:12:51,460 --> 00:12:52,620
That Liang boy thinks

259
00:12:52,620 --> 00:12:54,220
I look like a heavenly fairy.

260
00:12:55,310 --> 00:12:58,070
But that Big Madam Wu...

261
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,440
If you keep stewing over those things,

262
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:01,960
you can't stand out.

263
00:13:02,810 --> 00:13:04,330
Back then I

264
00:13:04,330 --> 00:13:06,250
made up my mind firmly too.

265
00:13:06,250 --> 00:13:06,950
I knew clearly that

266
00:13:06,950 --> 00:13:08,090
your father is softhearted

267
00:13:08,090 --> 00:13:08,930
and easily manipulated.

268
00:13:09,350 --> 00:13:11,190
That's how I fought for what we have today.

269
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:13,800
And you were born

270
00:13:13,800 --> 00:13:15,200
as the daughter of an official's house.

271
00:13:15,400 --> 00:13:16,920
So you ought to step out the door as a Sheng,

272
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:17,720
and go higher!

273
00:13:19,210 --> 00:13:20,450
The Countess doesn't want

274
00:13:20,450 --> 00:13:21,010
a concubine-born daughter,

275
00:13:21,010 --> 00:13:21,600
but it doesn't mean the Young Master

276
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,090
of the Count Yongchang Manor

277
00:13:22,090 --> 00:13:23,170
doesn't want a concubine's daughter either.

278
00:13:25,170 --> 00:13:26,130
You are right, Mother.

279
00:13:27,174 --> 00:13:28,014
I will go.

280
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,520
Now you're enlightened!

281
00:13:31,930 --> 00:13:32,890
For the rest of things,

282
00:13:33,332 --> 00:13:35,052
